      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading rates and fixture configurations; at minimum two load levels evaluated.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 standard fixture configuration at quasi-static displacement rate (5 mm/min). No variation in test block material, inter-screw distance, or loading rate was explored. This single test condition is insufficient to demonstrate robustness across the clinical loading envelope. Achieved Gradation 2 falls below the required Gradation 3; this gap is documented as an accepted limitation given the scope of the submission and the supporting analytical sensitivity analysis."
    },
    {
